## 4. JWT & Merchant ID Propagation (CRITICAL)

### Current Issue
Merchant ID from JWT token may not propagate correctly to B2B store, causing empty Pro interface.

### Required Backend Changes

#### 4.1. JWT Token Structure
**Current Token Payload:**
```json
{
  "user_id": "user-123",
  "phone": "+998901234567",
  "role": "user"  // or "merchant"
}
```

**Required Token Payload:**
```json
{
  "user_id": "user-123",
  "phone": "+998901234567",
  "role": "merchant",  // or "user", "admin"
  "merchant_id": "merchant-789",  // ADD THIS (if role=merchant)
  "business_ids": ["biz-456", "biz-457"]  // ADD THIS (all businesses owned)
}
```

#### 4.2. Token Refresh Endpoint
**Endpoint:** `POST /api/auth/refresh`

**Behavior:**
- Include `merchant_id` and `business_ids` in refreshed token
- If user has multiple businesses, include all in `business_ids`

#### 4.3. Merchant Context Endpoint
**New Endpoint:** `GET /api/merchants/me`

**Purpose:** Fetch current merchant context after login

**Response:**
```json
{
  "merchant_id": "merchant-789",
  "businesses": [
    {
      "id": "biz-456",
      "name": "Beauty Studio Pro",
      "is_active": true,
      "role": "owner"
    }
  ],
  "primary_business_id": "biz-456"
}
```

